      <h2 class="post-title">Bird Watching in Sigiriya Sanctuary</h2>
      <p class="post-meta">Published on May 23, 2023</p>
      <div class="post-content">
      <p>Sigiriya rock has a designated forest reserve and its very good destination to watch birds. King Kashyapa built his rock fortress in the 5th century so as to have a bird’s eye view of approaching enemies. Today, from its summit it is birds and wildlife the intrepid visitor sees. Sigiriya sanctuary is a well-protected UNESCO World heritage site. This is a heavenly place for birds with thick canopies and forests. Sigiriya is surrounded with vast manmade tanks and this has made it to become a place to witness large number of migratory and endemic birds.</p>  
